# Chessverse Guide (Requestable)

## Project
- Stack: Python 3.13 + FastAPI. Layout: api/, core/, models/, services/, tests/
- Logic in core/, not endpoints. Use .env, structured logging (no print), type hints

## AI Style
- Plan first (3–5 bullets), explain choice, types + docstrings, follow architecture
- Never: print(), globals, hardcoded paths, logic in endpoints
- Response: ## Plan → ## Implementation → ## Testing

## Stack
- FastAPI: Pydantic models, HTTPException, async/await, lifespan for resources
- Node/React: TypeScript, service layer, proper status codes

## Testing
- pytest ≥80%, mock externals, test errors. Naming: test_<fn>_<scenario>
- Unit: app/tests/unit/, Integration: TestClient, Engine: mock Stockfish

## Git
- Branch: feature/AI-XXX-desc, fix/AI-XXX-desc
- Commit: AI-XXX: imperative brief (≤50 chars)
- Pre-PR: ruff check/format, pyright, pytest --cov

## Kubernetes (bs-cluster)
- Before `kubectl` to **chessverse** namespaces: set `$env:KUBECONFIG` to the Rancher/Tailscale kubeconfig, or from monorepo root run `.\scripts\kubectl-bs.ps1 …` (defaults to `../keys/kubeconfig-rancher-ts.yaml`).
- Plain `kubectl` without that uses `%USERPROFILE%\.kube\config` and may hit a dead API host (e.g. old DigitalOcean).
